cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on analyzing the behavior of CNN architectures for image classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The study also involves understanding how invariances to certain transformations are learned, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper introduces a new learnable module, which involves optimization and neural networks (cs.NE), and the results could also be relevant for natural language processing (cs.CL) if the CNNs are applied to text classification tasks.
